title: BATMAN '66  021 (2013) (DC Comics) (digital) (Son of Ultron-Empi
description:
The Joker is back in action in DC Comics' digital-first series based on the Adam West/Burt Ward Batman television show, Batman '66.

Written by guest-scribe Tom Peyer with art by Derec Donovan, Chapter 21 of the series finds The Joker downsizing his crew of henchmen after realizing that the expense of being the Clown Prince of Crime sometimes outweighs the profit. Unfortunately for his goons, we can't imagine getting laid off by The Joker means they're going to be alive long enough to get unemployment.

Chapter 21 is dubbed "The Joker's Layoff Riot".
